"script": "Patients with crippling knee pain were wheeled into the operating room, put under, and cut open. The surgeon then repaired the damaged joint. But for some of them, the doctors did absolutely nothing. They just made the incision, sewed it back shut, and faked the entire operation. And here's the unbelievable part. Months later, the patients who got the fake surgery reported the exact same relief as the ones who got the real thing. They walked better. They hurt less. You see, simply believing they'd been healed was powerful enough to rewrite how their bodies actually felt the pain.",
